/*!
@defgroup tenbaset_phy TENBASET_PHY: 10BASE-T1S Digital PHY Driver
@details The MCUXpresso SDK provides a peripheral driver for the 10BASE-T1S Digital PHY (TENBASET_PHY)
         module of MCUXpresso SDK devices.

# TENBASET_PHY: 10BASE-T1S Digital PHY Driver {#TENBASET_PHYDigitalPHYDriver}

# Overview {#TENBASET_PHYOverview}

The TENBASET_PHY driver provides a comprehensive interface for configuring and managing the 10BASE-T1S Digital PHY.
It supports various operations including:
- Physical Layer Collision Avoidance (PLCA) configuration
- Mode control
- Wake configuration
- Interrupt management
- Diagnostic and status reporting

# Key Features {#TENBASET_PHYKeyFeatures}

- PLCA (Physical Layer Collision Avoidance) support
- Flexible mode transitions
- Wake-up configuration
- Serial Management Interface (SMI) access
- Comprehensive diagnostic capabilities

# Operations of TENBASET_PHY Digital PHY Driver {#TENBASET_PHYDriverOperations}

## Initialization {#TENBASET_PHYInitialization}

To use the TENBASET_PHY driver, follow these steps:
1. Get default configuration using @ref TENBASET_PHY_GetDefaultConfig
2. Modify configuration as needed
3. Initialize handle with @ref TENBASET_PHY_CreateHandle
4. Initialize the driver with @ref TENBASET_PHY_Init
5. Optionally set up interrupt handling

Example initialization flow:
- Call TENBASET_PHY_GetDefaultConfig to obtain default settings
- Modify PLCA configuration, wake settings, or interrupt mask
- Allocate tenbaset_phy_handle_t structure and call TENBASET_PHY_CreateHandle to initialize it
- Call TENBASET_PHY_Init with the configured parameters and handle pointer

## PLCA Configuration {#TENBASET_PHYPLCAConfiguration}

The driver supports detailed PLCA configuration:
- Set node ID and total node count
- Configure timers for transmission opportunities
- Enable or disable PLCA

Use @ref TENBASET_PHY_SetPLCAConfig to configure PLCA parameters
Use @ref TENBASET_PHY_GetPLCAConfig to retrieve current configuration

## Mode Control {#TENBASET_PHYModeControl}

Supports various mode transitions:
- Link Down
- Link Up
- Low Power
- Transceiver Configuration
- Built-In Self-Test (BIST)

Use @ref TENBASET_PHY_SetMode to change operational modes
Use @ref TENBASET_PHY_GetModeStatus to check current mode
Use @ref TENBASET_PHY_IsLinkUp to quickly check link status

## Wake Configuration {#TENBASET_PHYWakeConfiguration}

Configurable wake-up features:
- Remote and local wake events
- Wake forwarding
- Wake-up timeout configuration

Use @ref TENBASET_PHY_SetWakeConfig to configure wake settings
Use @ref TENBASET_PHY_TriggerWakeUp to initiate wake sequence
Use @ref TENBASET_PHY_GetWakeUpStatus to check wake-up status

## Interrupt Handling {#TENBASET_PHYInterruptHandling}

- Configurable interrupt sources
- Flexible interrupt enable/disable
- Status retrieval and clearing

Use @ref TENBASET_PHY_EnableInterrupts to set up interrupts
Use @ref TENBASET_PHY_GetInterruptStatus to check interrupt sources
Use @ref TENBASET_PHY_ClearInterruptStatus to manage interrupt flags

## Diagnostic Capabilities {#TENBASET_PHYDiagnostics}

Provides various diagnostic functions:
- PLCA diagnostic flags
- Transceiver diagnostic flags
- Counters for beacons, collisions, and jabber events

Use diagnostic functions like:
- @ref TENBASET_PHY_GetPLCADiagnosticFlags
- @ref TENBASET_PHY_GetTransceiverDiagnosticFlags
- @ref TENBASET_PHY_GetBeaconCounter

## SMI Interface {#TENBASET_PHYSMIInterface}

Supports Serial Management Interface (SMI) operations:
- Configuration of SMI parameters
- Read/Write to PHY registers of external PMD transceiver device

Use @ref TENBASET_PHY_SetMode to switch to transceiver configuration mode
Use @ref TENBASET_PHY_SetSMIConfig to configure SMI
Use @ref TENBASET_PHY_SMIRead and @ref TENBASET_PHY_SMIWrite for register access

# Typical Use Cases {#TENBASET_PHYUseCases}

## Basic Initialization and Link Establishment

1. Get default configuration
2. Modify PLCA and wake settings
3. Initialize driver
4. Set link up mode
5. Check link status

## Advanced PLCA Configuration

1. Configure node parameters
2. Set transmission opportunity timers
3. Enable PLCA
4. Initialize driver

## Wake-up Sequence

1. Configure wake settings
2. Set up interrupts
3. Trigger wake-up
4. Monitor wake-up status

*/
